vì chưa gõ kịp latex nên em tạm đưa đáp án lên đây trước ạ.

EX 1:
a group of people 5% of which are known to have Hansen's disease, in it_ 98% tested positive(po)
                                                                       _ 3% tested negative(ne)
A = {Hansen(H), Not(N)}
Use Baye's rule we have:
P(po|H) = ( P(H|po) * P(po) ) / P(H)
        = ( 0.05 * 0.98) / ( 0.05 * 0.98 + 0.05 * 0.0.03 )
        = 0.(9702)
